headline: 3 Reasons DAL is Risky and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: The past six months have been a windfall for Delta’s shareholders. The company’s stock price has jumped 41.1%, hitting $69.40 per share. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
